---
layout: layouts/base.njk
pageTitle: "About Mainstreet Benchmark"
metaDescription: "Mainstreet Benchmark publishes industry-specific SDE multiples and a free valuation calculator for small business owners. Derived from 9,500+ BizBuySell closed transactions across 63 industries."
canonicalPath: /about/
---

{% block schema %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "name": "About {{ site.brandName | jsStr }}",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}/about/",
  "description": "{{ site.brandName | jsStr }} publishes industry-specific SDE multiples and a free business valuation calculator for small business owners, derived from BizBuySell closed transaction data.",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "@id": "{{ site.url }}/#organization",
    "name": "{{ site.brandName | jsStr }}",
    "url": "{{ site.url }}/",
    "contactPoint": {
      "@type": "ContactPoint",
      "email": "{{ site.contactEmail }}",
      "contactType": "customer support"
    },
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "streetAddress": "{{ site.address.street }}",
      "addressLocality": "{{ site.address.city }}",
      "addressRegion": "{{ site.address.state }}",
      "postalCode": "{{ site.address.zip }}",
      "addressCountry": "US"
    }
  }
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ site.url }}/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "{{ site.url }}/about/" }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}

<nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
  <ol>
    <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li aria-current="page">About</li>
  </ol>
</nav>

<article class="about-page">
  <div class="container">

    <h1>About Mainstreet Benchmark</h1>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>What This Is</h2>
      <p>
        Mainstreet Benchmark is a free business valuation calculator and data reference for small business
        owners who want to know what their business is actually worth before talking to a broker.
        Every valuation uses industry-specific SDE multiples derived from real closed transaction data —
        not generic "2–4×" ranges that give you nothing useful.
      </p>
      <p>
        The data covers {{ site.transactionCount }}+ closed small business sales reported to BizBuySell
        (CoStar Group) from Q1 {{ site.dataCoverageStart }} through Q4 {{ site.dataCoverageEnd }}, across
        63 industries in 12 categories. These are actual sale prices — not asking prices — which is
        the only number that matters.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section" id="author">
      <h2>Who Builds This</h2>
      <div class="about-person">
        <h3>{{ site.author.name }} — Founder</h3>
        <p>{{ site.author.bio }}</p>
        <p>
          The idea for Mainstreet Benchmark came from a recurring observation: business owners preparing
          to sell consistently overestimate or underestimate their value because they have no access to
          industry-specific transaction data. Brokers have it. Buyers have it. Sellers don't.
          Mainstreet Benchmark closes that gap — no email required, no registration wall,
          no generic range that applies to nothing in particular.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section" id="reviewer">
      <h2>Data Review</h2>
      <p>
        Industry valuation data and calculator methodology are reviewed by a credentialed business
        transaction professional before publication. Reviewer credentials and bio will be published
        here prior to site launch.
      </p>
      <p>
        For questions about specific data or methodology, contact
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}">{{ site.contactEmail }}</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>What This Is Not</h2>
      <p>
        Mainstreet Benchmark is not a formal business appraisal service. The valuations produced by
        this calculator are planning estimates based on closed transaction data — useful for understanding
        market-rate pricing and preparing for broker conversations, but not a substitute for a formal
        appraisal for legal, tax, or financing purposes.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site does not provide broker referrals, does not capture or sell user data, and does not
        require any registration or email to use.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Data Source</h2>
      <p>
        All industry multiples are derived from
        <a href="{{ site.bizBuySellUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BizBuySell's Industry Valuation Report</a>
        (CoStar Group), the most comprehensive database of Main Street business transactions in the
        United States. BizBuySell reports closed transaction data — verified sale prices — not asking
        prices or broker estimates.
      </p>
      <p>
        The dataset is updated biannually as new BizBuySell data becomes available.
        Current data: {{ site.dataSource }}.
      </p>
      <p>
        For full methodology, including how multiples are calculated, how adjustment factors are derived,
        and how the calculator produces its range, see the
        <a href="/methodology/">Methodology page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}">{{ site.contactEmail }}</a><br>
        {{ site.address.full }}
      </p>
    </section>

  </div>
</article>

{% endblock %}
